It is understood that the wise speak of old things in new ways or tell us about new things in old ways.
In other words, according to Meade, we lack soul: “Soul is the glue of the world and the connecting principle of life…[it] connects us to things that are deep and abiding in the world and in our own lives.
In Awakening the Soul, you mention the individual soul and the Soul of the World.
I want to come back here.” The old idea is that you counted the soul of the place.
The old idea was that the world has a soul too—anima mundi would be the latin.